data.description: Deadline for all offers are by 7pm on Saturday. This stunning 4-bedroom, 3.5 bath Colonial, offers 3 finished levels in the desirable Dunligh community.  A rare double cul de sac  with a beautiful and breathtaking backyard (professionally landscaped), 2-car garage(NEWLY PAINTED,Epoxy ), wood deck(painted and sealed 2024),  are only some of the fine features that make this home so appealing!!Hardwood floors, recessed lighting, decorative moldings, an abundance of windows, finished lower level with plenty of storage, additional room and laundry room  create instant appeal. Rich classic floors welcome warmth from the sun filled foyer ushering right to your formal living room where large windows flood the space with natural light and illuminate decorative moldings and designer paint. The formal dining room is filled with natural light and crown molding. The kitchen with beautiful maple cabinets ,silestone countertops, island, SS Appliances, Gas stove, tile flooring, recessed lighting and sliding door that opens to beautiful deck and Garden.....Open concept kitchen to large  and bright family room , recessed lighting, wood burning fire place... This house is perfect for entertainment!The upstairs owner’s suite boasts  with beautiful hardwood floors three spacious closet and a walkin closet, luxurious primary bath with dual vanities, frameless glass shower, marble flooring. Down the hall, three additional bright and cheerful bedrooms with custom made closet in one of the bedrooms, separate stackable washer and dryer  in another complete this level. The lower-level recreation room/game room/exercise room is equipped with a full bathroom an extra room(office),laundry room to complete the comfort and luxury of this well thought floor plan home. This home boasts several notable updates: Roof 2019, Kitchen 2014,dishwasher 2023, powder room 2014, newly painted main level, Upper-level laundry 2023, 2 Zone AC 2023,stove 2017,Refrigerator 2021,water heater 2019,Freshly painted and sealed Deck 2024,Freshly painted Epoxy on the Garage floor, exterior was power washed 2024... Walking path to Lake braddock secondary school and Tot lot, shopping, library & bus stop to Pentagon. Less than 5 minutes to the VRE commuter train for those headed to DC
